      • addModule

        protected void addModule(AdapterModule<Adapter> module,
             int moduleID)

        Adds the given module into the current modules of this manager. If there is already some module with the same moduleIDl, the old module will be replaced by the new one.

        Parameters:
        module - Module to add.
        moduleID - Id by which can be the given module obtained from this manager.
        See Also:
        getModule(int)

      • getModule

        protected AdapterModule<Adapter> getModule(int moduleID)

        Returns a module added into this manager.

        Parameters:
        moduleID - Id of a module to obtain.
        Returns:
        The module which is represented by the given moduleID.
        See Also:
        addModule(com.wit.android.widget.adapter.module.AdapterModule, int)

      • removeModule

        protected void removeModule(int moduleID)

        Removes a module from the current modules set of this manager.

        Parameters:
        moduleID - Id of a module to remove.

      • dispatchSaveState

        protected void dispatchSaveState(android.os.Bundle outState)

        Called to save state of this manager instance. If the given outState is invalid, there will be created a new bundle and BaseMultiAdapter.onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle) will be invoked immediately.

        Parameters:
        outState - Outgoing state in which should this manager instance save its state.
        See Also:
        BaseMultiAdapter.onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle)

      • dispatchRestoreState

        protected void dispatchRestoreState(android.os.Bundle savedState)

        Called to restore state of this manager instance. If the given savedState is valid, BaseMultiAdapter.onRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle) will be invoked immediately.

        Parameters:
        savedState - Should be the bundle with saved state in BaseMultiAdapter.onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle).
        See Also:
        BaseMultiAdapter.onRestoreInstanceState(android.os.Bundle)
